headlines.description: — Devin Booker never tires of watching Chris Paul do his thing to lift Phoenix to big wins.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns hold off 76ers 114-109 for NBA-best 44th victory

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 34 points and the Atlanta Hawks regained their 3-point touch, overwhelming the trade-depleted Indiana Pacers 133-112 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young has 34 as Hawks crush trade-depleted Pacers, 133-112

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown and Marcus Smart each scored 22 points and the Boston Celtics rolled to their sixth straight win, beating the star-less Brooklyn Nets 126-91 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics romp to 126-91 win, star-less Nets drop 9th straight

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 30 points, Jaren Jackson Jr. added 26 points and 11 rebounds as the Memphis Grizzlies routed the Los Angeles Clippers 135-109 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant tallies 30 points again as Grizzlies rout Clippers.

events.name: Houston Rockets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram and the New Orleans Pelicans acknowledged that the emotions that came with losing teammates they care about personally in a significant trade might have contributed to a slow start against the reeling Houston Rockets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram scores 26, surging Pelicans top Rockets 110-97

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 33 points with 11 assists while coming up three rebounds shy of his third consecutive triple-double, Jalen Brunson scored 21 points and the Dallas Mavericks overwhelmed the Detroit Pistons 116-86 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's 33 points, 11 assists lead Mavs past Pistons 116-86

events.name: New York Knicks at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Rookie Bones Hyland scored 22 points, Nikola Jokic had 21 and the Denver Nuggets beat New York 132-115 on Tuesday night, sending the Knicks to a fourth consecutive loss and the 10th in their last 12 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hyland scores 22 points, Nuggets beat Knicks 132-115

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 44 points on 17-for-20 shooting, and Bobby Portis had 23 points with five 3-pointers in the Milwaukee Bucks' 131-116 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis scores 44, leads Bucks' 131-116 win over Lakers

events.name: Orlando Magic at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony scored 23 points and the Orlando Magic downed the Trail Blazers 113-95 on Tuesday night, hours after a trade ended ended guard CJ McCollum's nearly nine-year tenure in Portland.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic down Blazers 113-95 after Portland deals away McCollum
